    {
      "content": {
        "body": "## Problem\n`price_volume.parquet` contains unadjusted prices. Stock splits create false signals downstream in kr-derivatives.\n\n- Ticker 224060 shows moneyness 334x (stock split artifact)\n- 254 rows with moneyness >10x are contaminated\n- kr-derivatives Run 1 flag rate is 49.3% (should be <35% after fix)\n\n## Fix\nUse pykrx `stock.get_market_ohlcv_by_date` with `adjusted=True` flag.\n\n## Verification\nAfter fix, moneyness >10x count should drop from 254 to <20.\n\n## Cross-reference\n- Discovered in: kr-derivatives Run 1 (`reports/first_run_lessons.md`)\n- Detailed plan: kr-derivatives `reports/second_run_prep.md` (Change 1)\n- Tracked as: XB-001 in forensic-accounting-toolkit",
        "number": 1,
        "repository": "pon00050/krff-shell",
        "title": "Fix: use split-adjusted prices in extract_price_volume.py",
        "type": "Issue",
        "url": "https://github.com/pon00050/krff-shell/issues/1"
      },
